Subject: Codex LM Studio Worker Packet Template

Description: Template for context streams, LM Studio manager proposals, OpenAI Codex worker packets, and result captures.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\CodexLMStudioOrchestrationWorkspace.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SOPWorkerBootPacket.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\TaskFrameLaunchQueue.sop

& [CodexContextStreamPacketShape] is the packet Codex writes for LM Studio manager attention
  + [packet_id] is stable context stream identifier
  + [source_authority] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop plus cited source documents
  + [focus_subject] is current task focus
  + [task_frame] is subject, objective, reminders, allowed surface, blocked surface, and return anchor
  + [source_slice_set] is the minimal SOP files or excerpts needed for the manager pass
  + [compiled_attention_kernel] is selected attention patterns when needed
  + [queue_state] is current ready, blocked, running, or returned candidates
  + [expected_manager_output] is codex_job_proposal or blocked_outside note
  + [evidence_gate] is proof required before integration
  + [outside] is blocked work, uncertainty, credentials, hidden state, unrelated files, and forbidden launch

  = must: be compact enough for the selected LM Studio context window
  = must: include enough source to prevent adjacent project rails from becoming task authority
  = must: carry outside explicitly

& [LMStudioManagerProposalShape] is the exact output expected from the local manager
  + [proposal_id] is stable proposal identifier
  + [proposed_worker_lane] is openai_codex_cli, manual, deferred, or blocked
  + [objective] is one bounded job for OpenAI Codex or blocked_outside reason
  + [working_directory] is the proposed Codex CLI working root
  + [allowed_surface] is files, commands, tests, and sources the worker may use
  + [blocked_surface] is forbidden files, actions, claims, credentials, and unrelated dirty files
  + [prompt_packet_refs] is context stream and source references to include
  + [capture_target] is where worker output should be captured
  + [proof_gate] is tests, diff, citations, validation, or review required before integration
  + [risk_gate] is cost, authority, safety, destructive action, and stop policy
  + [outside] is residual uncertainty or blocked launch material

  = must: propose exactly one job or one blocked_outside note
  = must: remain non-mutating proposal text
  = must: avoid claiming launch, completion, commit, push, or integration

& [OpenAICodexWorkerPacketShape] is the packet Codex may send to OpenAI-backed Codex CLI
  + [worker_packet_id] is stable worker packet identifier
  + [approved_by] is Codex launch review
  + [objective] is one bounded implementation or specification task
  + [source_refs] is files and source documents that govern the job
  + [allowed_surface] is explicit workspace, files, commands, tests, and outputs
  + [blocked_surface] is unrelated dirty files, credentials, destructive commands, and unapproved remote actions
  + [expected_changes] is the intended files or no-file output
  + [capture_target] is where final worker message and proof should be stored
  + [proof_gate] is validation needed before integration
  + [return_schema] is changed files, tests, summary, outside, and next step

  = must: be reviewed before launch
  = must: be captured before integration
  = must: preserve outside and stop on authority conflict

& [ResultCaptureRecordShape] is the record that turns returned work into task narrative
  + [capture_id] is stable capture identifier
  + [source_proposal] is LM Studio proposal or manual task frame that led to launch
  + [worker_packet] is approved OpenAI Codex worker packet
  + [raw_output] is captured worker message or blocked note
  + [diff_summary] is changed files and intended meaning
  + [validation] is test, diff check, ASCII scan, validator score, or review result
  + [integration_disposition] is integrate, revise, retry, reject, defer, or preserve_outside
  + [commit_report] is file count, commit id, version, local/remote status, and push status when committed
  + [next_step] is the next safe visible action or stop reason
  + [outside] is unresolved risk, missed work, blocked authority, failed validation, or unrelated worktree state

  = must: separate raw output from integration disposition
  = must: connect captures back to queue, manager state, focal point, and operating-loop tick
